title: US men lock up spot in world gymnastics finals after gritty performance in qualifying
text:
US men lock up spot in world gymnastics finals after gritty performance in qualifying By WILL GRAVES AP Sports Writer First Posted: October 26, 2015 - 3:26 pmLast Updated: October 26, 2015 - 3:26 pm We also have more stories about: (click the phrases to see a list) 
People: 
United Kingdom (463) 
GLASGOW, Scotland â€” The U.S. men's gymnastics team advanced to the world championship finals with a gritty performance in qualifying on Monday. 
The Americans, competing without injured stars Sam Mikulak, Jake Dalton and John Orozco, posted a team score of 350.332. That's good enough for fifth with one more qualifying session to go. The top eight teams advance to Wednesday's final and secure an automatic spot in the 2016 Olympics. 
Danell Leyva led the way with an all-around total of 88.898, including an impressive 15.566 on the high bar to lock up a spot in the event finals this weekend. 
The U.S. had to hold on at the end, with Alex Naddour's 15.266 on pommel horse giving the Americans just enough to slip into fifth ahead of Switzerland.
